manjaro install mysql

sudo pacman -S mysql

initialize mysql

sudo mysqld --initialize --user=mysql --basedir=/usr --datadir=/var/lib/mysql

then will generate a root password like
```
A temporary password is generated for root@localhost: TeebGKOLT6!L

```

sudo systemctl start mysqld

then connect the mysql

mysql -u root -p

then input the generate password

edit the root password by a easy way use command

```
mysqladmin -u root -p password  xxxx(your new passowrd)
```
